A very colorfully-written account of the April 18, 1914 game at Ebbets Field contains this:

&quot;The only bit of ceremony that took place was the presentation of a traveling bag to Catcher Dick Cotter of the Giants. Dick lives in these parts, so the boys he pals with chipped in and got him a bag which is plenty big enough to carry Dick's collars and toothbrush.&quot;

